The telephone was invented by Alexander Graham Bell in 1876. Bell was a Scottish-born inventor and scientist who worked with electrical signals and communication devices. He patented the telephone on March 7, 1876, and made the first successful telephone call on March 10 of that year, saying "Mr. Watson, come here, I want to see you." The telephone revolutionized communication and paved the way for many future inventions and innovations in the field of telecommunications.